  <!--   Chapter  2   -->
  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="2" style="c" sid="1TI 2" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="1TI 2:1" />I urge <char style="it">that </char>first above all <char style="it">else</char> <char style="it">you</char>
        offer supplications (i.e., urgent requests), prayers (i.e., generic prayers), intercessions (i.e., a
        two-way exchange in prayer), and giving of thanks<char style="sup">[A]</char>for all people, <verse eid="1TI 2:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="1TI 2:2" />for kings and for every high-ranking official, so that we may spend our time leading a quiet (i.e., free
        of disturbances, crises, unrest, etc.) and tranquil life in piety and dignity in every respect. <verse eid="1TI 2:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="1TI 2:3" />This is a good thing to do, is acceptable, pleasing, and welcomed when examined by<char style="sup">[a]</char>
        God our Savior, <verse eid="1TI 2:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="1TI 2:4" />Who wants all people to be saved and to come to the knowledge and understanding of the truth. <verse eid="1TI 2:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="1TI 2:5" />The fact of the matter is that there is one God <char style="it">and there is </char>one mediator between
        God and mankind, <char style="it">the</char> man Christ Jesus, <verse eid="1TI 2:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="1TI 2:6" />who gave himself <char style="it">to be</char> an atonement<char style="sup">[b]</char>—the price of
        redemption; the price to buy someone back—for everyone, <char style="it">to be </char>that which serves
        as proof or makes a solemn statement in every individual period of human history<char style="sup">[c]</char>—<verse eid="1TI 2:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="1TI 2:7" />For which I was appointed a preacher and an apostle (i.e., a missionary)—I’m telling you the truth—no
        lie—an instructor of Gentiles in what true faith really is<char style="sup">[d]</char>.<verse eid="1TI 2:7" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="1TI 2:8" />After some careful thought, I desire that men in every place pray and pray, lifting up holy hands, keeping
        a distance from anger and plotting. <verse eid="1TI 2:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="1TI 2:9" />Likewise, <char style="it">I desire that</char> women dress themselves in good taste<char style="sup">[e]</char>
        <char style="it">and choose an attire </char>with modesty and good judgment combined with self-control,
        not <char style="it">dress themselves </char>in an <char style="it">exotic</char> hairstyle<char style="sup">[f]</char>
        and with <char style="it">ultra-expensive </char>gold <char style="it">jewelry</char> or pearls or expensive
        clothing<char style="sup">[B]</char>, <verse eid="1TI 2:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="1TI 2:10" />but instead <char style="it">I desire that they make themselves beautiful </char>(which is befitting
        to women sworn to a life of piety to God) by good works.<verse eid="1TI 2:10" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="1TI 2:11" />Have a woman<char style="sup">[C]</char> learn in silence with total submissiveness<char style="sup">[D]</char>;<verse eid="1TI 2:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="1TI 2:12" />I don’t permit a woman to give instructions <char style="it">for what a person should or shouldn’t do</char><char
        style="sup">[E]</char>, dominate, or give orders to a man, but rather <char style="it">it is for her
        </char>to be in silence. <verse eid="1TI 2:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="1TI 2:13" />The fact of the matter is that Adam was first formed <char style="it">out of clay in the Garden of Eden</char>,
        then Eve <char style="it">was formed</char>. <verse eid="1TI 2:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="1TI 2:14" />Plus Adam was not deceived <char style="it">by the serpent </char>but the woman <char style="it">was
        deceived</char>, <char style="it">and </char>once deceived, found herself<char style="sup">[g]</char>
        in transgression<char style="sup">[F]</char>. <verse eid="1TI 2:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="1TI 2:15" />But she will be spared calamity<char style="sup">[G]</char> through the childbearing <char style="it">years
        </char>if she were to continue in faith, love, and holiness with good judgment combined with self-control<char
        style="sup">[h]</char>.<verse eid="1TI 2:15" />
    </para>
