  <chapter number="4" style="c" sid="1TI 4" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="1TI 4:1" />The Spirit says explicitly that in later periods of human history<char style="sup">[a]</char> some will
        revolt<char style="sup">[b]</char> from the Faith, their attention occupied by deceiving spirits and
        doctrines or teachings of demons, <verse eid="1TI 4:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="1TI 4:2" />telling lies in hypocrisy, having reached the point where they’ve seared their own conscience, <verse eid="1TI 4:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="1TI 4:3" />hindering or preventing getting married, abstaining from foods that God created to be taken <char style="it">and
        consumed</char> with thanksgiving by those who believe and have perceived, recognized, and understood
        the truth. <verse eid="1TI 4:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="1TI 4:4" /><char style="it">And they are free to partake </char>because God’s entire creation is excellent, and
        nothing which is received with thanksgiving is to be rejected, <verse eid="1TI 4:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="1TI 4:5" />for <char style="it">the food which you eat </char>is designated holy on account of <char style="it">the
        </char>word of God and <char style="it">on account of </char>a request offered in prayer.<verse eid="1TI 4:5" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="1TI 4:6" />By teaching the comrades<char style="sup">[c]</char> these things until they’re built into them, you’ll
        be a fine minister<char style="sup">[d]</char> of Christ Jesus, firming up the words of the Faith and
        of the quality teaching which you have closely followed. <verse eid="1TI 4:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="1TI 4:7" />Refuse to receive <char style="it">things which are </char>profane and desecrated, <char style="it">things
        which are </char>old wives’ tales. Put yourself on a training program (like you do at the gym) towards
        <char style="it">building yourself up in </char>piety. <verse eid="1TI 4:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="1TI 4:8" />Physical training, you see, is beneficial to a small degree, but piety is beneficial in every respect,
        holding a promise of life (i.e., that special fullness of life) in the present time and in the time to
        come.<verse eid="1TI 4:8" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="1TI 4:9" />You can count on <char style="it">that</char> statement <char style="it">I just made </char>being true,
        and it deserves to be accepted any way you look at it. <verse eid="1TI 4:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="1TI 4:10" />In fact we work hard and strive for this, since we have set our hope on <char style="it">the </char>Living
        God, Who is <char style="it">the </char>Savior of all people, especially those who believe.<verse eid="1TI 4:10" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="1TI 4:11" />Charge <char style="it">the comrades with</char> these things and instruct <char style="it">them in them</char>.<verse eid="1TI 4:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="1TI 4:12" />Don’t let anyone think less of you or treat you disrespectfully because you’re young, but instead become
        an example for the believers <char style="it">to follow</char> in speech, in manner, in love, in faith,
        in purity (<char style="it">and the list goes on</char>).<verse eid="1TI 4:12" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="1TI 4:13" />Stay busy with <char style="it">Scripture </char>reading, with exhortation and encouragement, with teaching
        (<char style="it">and the list goes on</char>) until I get there. <verse eid="1TI 4:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="1TI 4:14" />Don’t neglect the <char style="it">spiritual </char>gift<char style="sup">[e]</char> in you which was
        given to you through prophecy and accompanied by the laying on of hands by the elders (i.e., the church
        board). <verse eid="1TI 4:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="1TI 4:15" />Put these things <char style="it">I’m writing to you about </char>into practice; be in them (i.e., be
        totally into them), so that your progress will be quite noticeable to everyone. <verse eid="1TI 4:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="1TI 4:16" />Pay close attention to yourself—how you are and what you do—and to your doctrine and teaching. Immerse
        yourself in them. You see, by so doing, you’ll be preserving yourself, protecting yourself, and keeping
        yourself from harm, you and those who listen to you.<verse eid="1TI 4:16" />
    </para>
